What you need to know:

Answering a question about whether he had ambitions to be FIFA president, Motsepe said: "Absolutely not. Infantino is doing a great job and must be supported."FIFA-brokered talks played a significant role in the election of Motsepe, who was chosen after his rivals, Ivorian Jacques Anouma, Mauritanian Ahmed Yahya and Senegalese Augustin Senghor, withdrew.Yahya and Senghor will become vice-presidents of the Cairo-based organisation and Anouma a special advisor to Motsepe.